Description: Fragment of round handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora from neck join to sharp turn. Clay fine pink-buff; cream slip. Circular stamp with rose symbol.
Curator's comments: Name Leontidas. Trimmed. Probably from same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, 0169.52.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1117)
